1 course formulated for a school district and approved by the state board.
2 (c)(1) The Division of Elementary and Secondary Education shall
3 establish and maintain a statewide, centralized, easily accessible online
4 portal for parents, school faculty, and school staff to access instructional
5 materials, if funding is available.
6 (2) The portal required by subdivision (c)(1) of this section
7 shall provide curriculum transparency that enables a parent to:
8 (A) Search and view instructional materials that are
9 searchable by district, school, and grade level;
10 (B) Review summaries of the content of each textbook used
11 by a district;
12 (C) Search and view the full content of each textbook used
13 by a district;
14 (D) Search and view library media materials used by each
15 school in a district; and
16 (E) Review a school's library media materials and opt out
17 his or her child from accessing library media materials the parent does not
18 wish to be available for his or her child.
19 (3) The portal required by subdivision (c)(1) of this section
20 shall enable a school administrator, school faculty member, and school staff
21 member to:
22 (A) Have uniform access to Arkansas school standards in a
23 single repository to ensure transparency and reduce ambiguity; and
24 (B) Reduce school employee workload by placing all
25 instructional materials in a centralized, searchable database.
26 (4) The portal required by subdivision (c)(1) of this section
27 shall enable a school administrator to comply with changing rules and
28 requirements by creating a database that contains school policies and
29 automatically updates based on changing rules and requirements.
30 (d) As used in this section:
31 (1) "District" means an Arkansas public kindergarten through
32 grade twelve (K-12) school district;
33 (2) "Instructional material" means a textbook, workbook, library
34 book, a library media material, a laboratory material, computer software,
35 video, or tape;
36 (3) "Library media material" means print and nonprint material
